Approach What you add to <code>mkdocs.yml</code> How you write a diagram in Markdown Pros Cons 1 · Client-side compile with TikZJax <code>yaml\nextra_css:\n  - https://tikzjax.com/v1/fonts.css\nextra_javascript:\n  - https://tikzjax.com/v1/tikzjax.js\n</code> <code>markdown\n&lt;script type=\"text/tikz\"&gt;\n\\usepackage{circuitikz}\n\\begin{circuitikz}\n\\draw (0,0) to[R,l=$1\\,\\mathrm{k}\\Omega$] (3,0) to[C,l=$10\\,\\mu\\text{F}$] (6,0)\n      (6,0) -- (6,-2) -- (0,-2) -- (0,0);\n\\end{circuitikz}\n&lt;/script&gt;\n</code> Nothing to install; live preview still instant with <code>mkdocs serve</code>; diagrams stay as clean SVG First render happens in the reader’s browser → page load gets slower if you embed dozens of large schematics; needs JS enabled; relies on external CDN (can self-host) (tikzjax.com, GitHub) 2 · Pre-compile to SVG during the MkDocs build <code>yaml\nplugins:\n  - search\n  - tikzfig  # custom plugin shown below\n</code> <code>markdown\n</code>circuitikz\n\draw (0,0) to[sV,l=$V_s$] (0,3) -- (3,3)\n            to[R,l=$R$]      (3,0) -- (0,0);\n``` Pages load instantly (SVG already generated); works with JS disabled; assets are cached, so rebuilds after edits are fast You install a TeX engine (<code>tectonic</code>) + <code>dvisvgm</code>; need to drop the tiny plugin file into your repo Minimal custom plugin (<code>plugins/tikzfig.py</code>) for option 2 <pre><code># pip install tectonic
# pip install mkdocs
import hashlib, os, re, subprocess, tempfile, textwrap
from mkdocs.plugins import BasePlugin

class TikzFigPlugin(BasePlugin):
    BLOCK = re.compile(r'```circuitikz(.*?)```', re.S)

    def on_page_markdown(self, md, page, cfg, files):
        def _repl(m):
            body = m.group(1).strip()
            digest = hashlib.md5(body.encode()).hexdigest()
            rel_svg = f'assets/tikz/{digest}.svg'
            abs_svg = os.path.join(cfg["site_dir"], rel_svg)
            if not os.path.exists(abs_svg):
                tex = textwrap.dedent(f"""
                \\documentclass[border=1pt]{{standalone}}
                \\usepackage{{circuitikz}}
                \\begin{document}
                \\begin{{circuitikz}}[american]
                {body}
                \\end{{circuitikz}}
                \\end{document}
                """)
                with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as d:
                    tex_file = os.path.join(d, "fig.tex")
                    open(tex_file, "w").write(tex)
                    subprocess.run(["tectonic", "-Z", "shell-escape", tex_file], cwd=d, check=True)
                    subprocess.run(["dvisvgm", "--no-fonts", "fig.dvi", "-o", abs_svg], cwd=d, check=True)
            return f'![]({{ static }}{rel_svg})'
        return self.BLOCK.sub(_repl, md)
</code></pre>
